text.tspan: Gender gap in hourly wages vs. Ratio of female-to-male labor force
The vertical axis shows the unadjusted gender wage gap calculated as the difference between average hourly earnings of men
and average hourly earnings of women expressed as a percentage of average hourly earnings of men. The horizontal axis
shows the ratio of female to male labor force participation rates (participation rates correspond to the proportion of the
population ages 15 and older that is economically active).
Ratio of female to male labor force participation rate (%) (modeled ILO estimate)
